## Purpose
The `frontend` module outlines the user-facing interfaces and developer tooling required to interact with MCP workflows. This includes CLI agents, prompt test runners, and Phase 2 dashboard concepts.

---

## Key Responsibilities
- CLI utilities for triggering MCP flows
- HITL token injection tools
- Prompt debugging and regression tools
- LangGraph test visualizer (Phase 2)
- MVP developer support, not customer UI

---

## Technologies
- Node.js (LTS)
- Typescript
- Jest (for testing)
- zx / Commander (CLI framework)
- REST or JSON-RPC client bindings for MCP

---

## Directory Layout
```
frontend/
├── cli/                  # CLI tools: `tenure run`, `tenure hitl`, etc.
├── prompts/              # Static prompt libraries used in agents
├── langgraph/            # Flow runners, visualizers (future)
├── tests/                # Prompt tests, CLI tests
├── manifest/             # HITL token logs, audit trails
└── .env                  # Frontend-specific bindings
```

---

## CLI Contracts
- `tenure run [flow] [params]` – triggers LangGraph flow
- `tenure hitl approve [token]` – injects HITL token into gateway
- `tenure prompt test` – runs regression tests on prompt outputs

---

## Constraints
- No web UI in MVP
- LangGraph visual tooling deferred to Phase 2
- HITL tokens passed manually or via CLI flags

---

## Developer Experience Goals
- Zero-config CLI tool for ops/dev
- Reproducible agent runs
- Versioned prompt debugging framework
- Eventual dashboard surface for approvals and traces
